<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFC7FFECFF8DFF3AFE53FDE3" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC7FFECFF8DFF3AFCCEFEC3" blockId="29.[113,1089,220,627]" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFF8DFF3AFF5EFF43" bold="true" box="[113,224,220,243]" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFF1BFF3AFE71FF43" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[231,463,220,243]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calvata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFF1BFF3AFE71FF43" box="[231,463,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">Mesomphalia calvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was until now an enigmatic species to cassidinae workers and was listed only in catalogues and last assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFCD1FF1AFB83FEA3" authority="(BOROWIEC 1999 a)" baseAuthorityName="BOROWIEC" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[813,1085,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFCD1FF1AFCD0FEA3" box="[813,878,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">Stolas</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC7FFECFC82FF1AFB8BFEA3" author="BOROWIEC" box="[894,1077,252,275]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC7FFECFEFBFEFAFEDAFE83" box="[263,356,284,307]" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">holotype</typeStatus>
of the species has broad ultimate tarsomere and belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFC1CFEFAFB84FE83" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1905" box="[992,1082,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFC1CFEFAFB84FE83" box="[992,1082,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">Agenysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In my opinion it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFE04FEDAFC8FFEE3" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1916" box="[504,817,316,339]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="connectens" subSpecies="aequatoriensis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFE04FEDAFC8FFEE3" box="[504,817,316,339]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. connectens aequatoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is, however, very different from typical 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFEA1FEBAFE4FFEC3" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[349,497,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connectens">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFEA1FEBAFE4FFEC3" box="[349,497,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. connectens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it has high reticulation on elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC7FFECFF6CFE9AFE86FDA3" blockId="29.[113,1089,220,627]" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">
It is possible that 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFEB1FE9AFE04FE23" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[333,442,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calvata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFEB1FE9AFE04FE23" box="[333,442,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. calvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific also with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFD3DFE9AFBBAFE23" authority="(Boheman, 1862)" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[705,1028,380,403]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacertosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFD3DFE9AFCFFFE23" box="[705,833,380,403]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. lacertosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC7FFECFCACFE9AFC42FE23" author="Boheman" box="[848,1020,380,403]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" refId="ref48022" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1862: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Quartus. (Supplementum). Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, vi + 504 pp." type="book" year="1862">Boheman, 1862</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFBD6FE9AFE33FE03" authority="Spaeth, 1905" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassicornis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFBD6FE9AFF4DFE03" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. crassicornis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC7FFECFF00FE7AFE33FE03" author="Spaeth" box="[252,397,412,435]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" pagination="79 - 118" refId="ref50803" refString="SPAETH F. 1905: Beschreibung einiger neuer Cassiden nebst synonymischen Bemerkungen V. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 55: 79 - 118." type="journal article" year="1905">Spaeth, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), which might represent only a montane form with black elytra while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFF48FE5AFE9FFE63" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[180,289,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calvata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFF48FE5AFE9FFE63" box="[180,289,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. calvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always has a red reticulation on explanate margin of elytra. However, this problem requires further study and I provisionally consider both, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFCE3FE3AFC34FE43" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[799,906,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calvata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFCE3FE3AFC34FE43" box="[799,906,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. calvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC7FFECFC46FE3AFB84FE43" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[954,1082,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacertosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC7FFECFC46FE3AFB84FE43" box="[954,1082,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">A. lacertosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC7FFECFF6CFDFAFE53FDE3" blockId="29.[113,1089,220,627]" pageId="29" pageNumber="304">This species is distributed in the northern part of the Andes and adjacent foothills mostly on eastern slopes or central valleys.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
